    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architectural ornaments, formed of two or more interwoven bands which wind around a series of central points, often left blank. This type of decorative frieze is characteristic of Greek and Roman architecture and borders of Roman mosaics. </Note_Text>
